I have latest Pathlanner and PathPlannerLib, problem is I can’t define RobotConfig, and “AutoBuilder.configure()” is not even a thing.

When I try to define RobotConfig as this:

  RobotConfig config = RobotConfig.fromGUISettings();

It gives two error:

Unhandled exception type IOExceptionJava(16777384)
Unhandled exception type ParseExceptionJava(16777384)

And when I try to implement “AutoBuilder.configure()”, It does not even shows up as a method.

Robot Code is here: Github

I tried deleting and downloading Pathplanner/PathplannerLib and opening a new project, neither worked.

Wait a minute, sorry I didn’t read what the picture said properly. It is an unhandled exception which means you need to “handle” it. Pathplanner documentation has an example of how one might do so. I mixed this problem up with one I have experienced before, that is my bad. The try/catch code blocks are a way to handle it. Basically, it runs the code in the try block, and if it errors out, the code in the catch block is ran.

Have you opened up PathPlanner GUI and pointed it at your project? It will automatically place some test objects into your robot project, and save the config as well. You’ll end up with a settings.json file created on the first run of the PathPlanner GUI.
